</section>


  


















 



   <section id="water" class="why_matter content-paragraph paragraph-container">
    <div class="species_image species_image_reverse">
        <picture >
                <img loading="lazy" src="/sites/default/files/styles/content_slide_image/public/2017-06/Rain%20on%20leaf.jpg?h=af64fd07&amp;itok=UhiAYHjg" width="1000" height="600" alt="" title="Rain drops on leaf" class="image-style-content-slide-image" />




        </picture>

                <div class="copyright--image">© WWF-Canada/Frank Parhizgar</div>
            </div>
    <div class="content content--padded content_reverse">
            <h3>

<div class="field field--display_title">
  <h2>Water</h2>
</div>
</h3>
            <div class="rich-text-wrapper">
          <p>Water is an important natural resource so we try to use as little as possible in our offices.</p>
<p>The Living Planet Centre uses recycled&nbsp;rainwater and greywater (from sinks and showers)&nbsp;to flush the toilets and water the plants. This system reduces&nbsp;the mains water we use by over 50%.&nbsp;A leak detection system means we find out about leaks quickly, limiting the water lost.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Features like&nbsp;dual flush toilets, automatic taps in bathrooms and 'zip' taps in kitchens also help reduce water usage.</p>


      </div>
              

          <div class="btn-wrap">
                          
                   

